description: We offer full weekend rentals for weddings. We believe this provides the best option to allow you to have the rehearsal, rehearsal dinner, and decorating on Friday, the wedding on Saturday, and cleanup on Sunday. Our current cost for 2026 weddings is $6,500.00 for the weekend which will begin from Friday at 9:00am through Sunday at 12:00pm. Sales tax will be added to all rentals. Luckily, all we require to reserve your requested date is a $1,000.00 deposit that is deducted from the total cost of the venue. We take cash, checks, debit and credit cards - Visa, Mastercard, Discover, or American Express. All balances must be paid in full 60 days before your event, however, we allow you to make payments at any time for however much you desire! Once you book, we allow you to use the facility for engagement pictures or bridal portraits.  The following amenities are included in the barn rental listed by the area they are located:  Chapel:  Stained Glass Windows  LED Candles  Dimmed Lighting Capacity: 180 guests seated for ceremony.  Saloon:  Convection Oven Four Eye Stove Two Cocktail Refrigerators Wine Cooler Dishwasher Sink 10 - Bar Stools 9 - Saddle Stools 4 - Cocktail Tables TV with DVD Player Surround System Corral:  Women‚Äôs Restroom Shower Men‚Äôs Restroom Full Size Refrigerator  Storage Closet 2 - Large opening barn doors into grassy open fields. Most used for wedding ceremonies.   Patio or Elongated Decking Area: 15 - 5‚Äô X 6‚Äô Picnic Tables ; Seats 96 people if 6 per table  Firepit  Adjoining Cemented Shelter (Dance Floor) ; Capacity: 250 guests seated for ceremony.  Vintage Beverage Wagon Corn Hole Game Also Included:  20 - 5‚Äô Round Banquet Tables 5 - 8‚Äô Rectangle Serving Tables 155 - White Padded Folding Chairs Engagement Photography Sessions Bridal Portraits  Meetings with selected vendors Paper Towels Bathroom Tissue Trashbags  Hand Soaps  Trash Cans Propane Heaters at an additional $35 charge each to use - we provide propane tanks Firewood The Gentry Barn is 6,500 square feet and sits on approximately 260 beautiful acres. This heaven sent property also hosts a home for The Gentry Cabin, longhorns, horses, geese, and crops. We also have a large area for parking which has street light posts for nightly lighting.  The Gentry Farm‚Äôs quaint cabin includes 1 king bed, 1 bathroom with a shower, a kitchen area with a full size refrigerator, dining area, and a den. The Cabin makes for the picture perfect scenery for the bridal suite during the get ready process. The cabin is on the same property for $450.00 for the weekend, Friday from 9:00am through Sunday at 12:00pm. There is a surround sound system located in the barn with individual room controls. We are handicap accessible, with a removable ramp available upon request. You would be responsible for putting up tables and chairs, moving items back in place, and removing trash at the end of the event. description: This one's for you, new grads. üéì The best cities to start your career have been ranked by WalletHub, using over two dozen metrics ranging from job growth rate and starting salary averages to average commute and housing affordability. ‚ÄúThe best cities for starting a career not only have a lot of job opportunities but also provide substantial income growth potential and satisfying work conditions,‚Äù WalletHub analyst Chip Lupo said. ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs also important to consider factors such as how fun a city is to live in or how good of a place it is for raising a family, to ensure life satisfaction outside of your career.‚Äù The release of the report comes as graduation season is in full swing ‚Äì a time when many people are figuring out where in the country they want to kick off their professional lives. The five cities that WalletHub found to be most favorable for beginning a career were located in three different states. The cities of Charleston, South Carolina; Richmond, Virginia; Salt Lake City, Utah; Columbia, South Carolina; and Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania, are ranked No. 6 through 10, respectively. Of the 182 locales included in WalletHub‚Äôs report, the ones with the lowest overall scores for beginning a career were Detroit, Michigan; New York, New York; Oxnard, California; Bridgeport, Connecticut; and Pearl City, Hawaii.  üì∏: Getty; AP; Kevin Ruck - stock.adobe.com
